q-switch-case.body:
You have 5 possible commands: F, B, L, R, S. You could handle them with a chain of if-else:

```
if (cmd == 'F') motorForward();
else if (cmd == 'B') motorBack();
else if (cmd == 'L') motorLeft();
// ...etc
```

Or with a switch-case:

```
switch (cmd) {
  case 'F': motorForward(); break;
  case 'B': motorBack();    break;
  // ...etc
}
```

For a fixed set of single-character commands, which approach is better practice?

