q-safety-fix.body:
You've identified the problem: if communication drops, the robot runs away indefinitely.

The fix is a **timeout watchdog**: you record the timestamp of the last received command. In every `loop()` iteration, you check how long it's been since the last command. If it's been more than a threshold (say 200 ms), you automatically stop the motors — even if no `S` command was received.

```
unsigned long lastCmdTime = 0;

// In loop():
if (millis() - lastCmdTime > 200) {
  motorStop(); // Safety fallback
}

if (Serial.available()) {
  char cmd = Serial.read();
  lastCmdTime = millis(); // Reset watchdog
  handleCommand(cmd);
}
```

Now the robot stops automatically if no command arrives within 200 ms. What's the best fix from the options below?
